t platform provides robust and consistent data processing and management but is also flexible enough to accommodate new functionality and dimensions as necessary functional areas include manager due diligence and portfolio management accounting and back office operations risk management analytics and monitoring internal reporting client reporting specialized analytical procedures the optima it team first began implementation of the optima portfolio evaluation research  accounting system “operas” in  the platform makes our business more scalable as well as providing increased quantitative and qualitative value to the firm’s research process all research both data and documentbased is stored in operas and provides the research team with a solid platform on which to run various analytical programs additionally with the capability to run a wide variety of risk scenarios operas enables the investment operations and risks teams to holistically evaluate all aspects of a fund and the risks associated with its investments “we’ve worked diligently to develop a secure transparent and userfriendly technological platform in order to help our clients make informed investment decisions” arnold rozenvasser director xmllangenus langenus xmlnshttpwwwworgxhtml whyoptima registration client login english 〔〕 français españolas deutsch italiano  한국어 home our firm overview why optima th anniversary letter hedge magazine interview with dixon boardman dixon boardman profile in citywire our programs investment program investment process proprietary platform our team contact us accueil notre société vue densemble pourquoi optima th anniversary letter hedge magazine interview with dixon boardman dixon boardman profile in citywire nos programmes programme dinvestissement processus dinvestissement plateforme exclusive notre équipe nous contacter home unsere firma übersicht warum optima th anniversary letter hedge magazine interview with dixon boardman dixon boardman profile in citywire unsere pr